  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">A petting zoo sells two types of tickets. The standard ticket, for admission only, costs $5. The premium ticket, which includes admission and food to give to the animals, costs $12. One Saturday, the petting zoo sold a total of 250 tickets and collected a total of $2,300 from ticket sales. Which of the following systems of equations can be used to find the number of standard tickets, <span class=\"italic\">s</span>, and premium tickets, <span class=\"italic\">p</span>, sold on that Saturday?</p>\n",
